    <!-- Application Structure Plan: The SPA is designed as an interactive portfolio. A sticky navigation bar allows users (recruiters) to jump to key sections: Skills, Projects, Education. The core of the application is the 'Projects' section, which uses an interactive card layout. Clicking a card expands to show a detailed view with a conceptual flowchart and technologies used. This structure transforms the linear resume into an engaging, non-linear exploration, prioritizing user engagement and quick access to critical information. -->
    <!-- Visualization & Content Choices: 
        - Report Info: Technical Skills List -> Goal: Showcase proficiency -> Viz: Horizontal Bar Chart (Chart.js/Canvas) for visual comparison of self-assessed confidence levels. Interaction: Static but visually engaging.
        - Report Info: Projects List -> Goal: Detail project architecture & tech stack -> Viz: Interactive Cards. Interaction: Clicking a card triggers a JS function to expand a detailed view with a project flowchart (built with HTML/CSS) and tech tags, providing depth on demand.
        - Report Info: Education/Certs -> Goal: Present history -> Viz: Clean, styled lists/timeline layout. Interaction: None, purely informational.
        - Justification: This approach turns passive information into an interactive experience, encouraging exploration rather than just reading.
    -->
    <!-- CONFIRMATION: NO SVG graphics used. NO Mermaid JS used. -->
